						               													<description>Tricky War is a card game mixing predictive bid, trick-taking and war.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Tricky War, bid on uncertain duels and make the right choices to avoid losing too many points during the war phase.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Goal:&amp;#10;End up with the most &amp;ldquo;point&amp;rdquo; tokens when a player loses their last one.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Components:&amp;#10;- A 52-card deck (4 suits, each with cards from 1 to 13)&amp;#10;- 40 &amp;ldquo;point&amp;rdquo; tokens (you can also use a pen &amp;amp; paper)&amp;#10;- 20 &amp;ldquo;bidding&amp;rdquo; tokens (you can also use a pen &amp;amp; paper)&amp;#10;- Something to remember the trump suit(tokens, unused cards&amp;hellip;)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A game is played in several rounds. The game is over as soon as at least one player does not have any &amp;ldquo;point&amp;rdquo; tokens left.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A round is played in several phases:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1. Bidding&amp;#10;2. Choosing the trump suit&amp;#10;3. War&amp;#10;4. End of round&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When at least one player has lost all their &amp;ldquo;point&amp;rdquo; tokens, the game is over and the player who has the most &amp;quot;point&amp;quot; tokens is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules of Tricky come with some variants to add more control, a partnership mode and a solo mode.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
